---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Services" description="Real estate bookkeeping services for investors, property managers, and developers. Rental property accounting, catch-up bookkeeping, tax preparation support, and financial reporting.">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="section-heading">Real Estate Bookkeeping Services</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); max-width: 42rem;">Built specifically for real estate investors, property managers, and developers. Every service is designed to keep your portfolio finances organized and your business on track.</p>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Portfolio Bookkeeping</h3>
        <p>Ongoing bookkeeping for your entire real estate portfolio. We handle rental income tracking, property expense categorization, mortgage and loan reconciliation, and monthly financial statements for each entity or property.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Catch-Up Bookkeeping</h3>
        <p>Fallen behind on your property records? We'll work through your backlog, whether it's a few months or a few years, and bring everything current so you start fresh.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Tax Preparation Support</h3>
        <p>We organize your real estate financials and prepare the reports your CPA needs, including depreciation schedules, entity-level profit and loss statements, and Schedule E support. No more scrambling at tax time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Accounts Payable &amp; Receivable</h3>
        <p>Track rent collection, vendor payments, contractor invoices, and maintenance expenses across your portfolio. Stay on top of what you owe and what tenants owe you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Payroll Support</h3>
        <p>We help property management companies and development firms process payroll, track employee hours, and ensure payroll taxes are calculated correctly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Financial Reporting</h3>
        <p>Get clear, investor-ready reports including profit and loss by property, balance sheets, and cash flow statements. Delivered monthly so you always know where your portfolio stands.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- My Process -->
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">My Process</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); max-width: 42rem;">Every client goes through the same five-step process. It keeps things consistent, thorough, and predictable every month.</p>

    <div class="process-list">
      <div class="process-item">
        <div class="process-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/>
            <path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Connect &amp; Align</h3>
          <p>We start with a call to understand your portfolio structure, entity setup, and current state of your books. We connect your accounts, configure your chart of accounts for real estate, and establish a clear baseline.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="process-item">
        <div class="process-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/>
            <path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Clean &amp; Organize</h3>
          <p>If your books have gaps or inconsistencies, we work through them systematically. Every transaction is categorized correctly, every account is reconciled, and your records are brought up to date before we move forward.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="process-item">
        <div class="process-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/>
            <line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Maintain Weekly</h3>
          <p>We review and categorize new transactions every week so nothing accumulates or falls behind. This keeps your books current, catches errors early, and means month-end close is never a scramble.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="process-item">
        <div class="process-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <line x1="18" y1="20" x2="18" y2="10"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12" y2="4"/>
            <line x1="6" y1="20" x2="6" y2="14"/>
            <line x1="2" y1="20" x2="22" y2="20"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Close &amp; Review</h3>
          <p>By the 10th of each month, we close the prior month's books, reconcile all accounts, and prepare your financial statements. Every line is reviewed for accuracy before anything goes out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="process-item">
        <div class="process-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="23 6 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 1 18"/>
            <polyline points="17 6 23 6 23 12"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Deliver &amp; Improve</h3>
          <p>We deliver your monthly reports and stay available to answer questions. Over time, we look for ways to improve categorization, refine reporting by property or entity, and give you better financial visibility across your portfolio.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- How I Work With Your CPA -->
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">How I Work With Your CPA</h2>
    <div class="cpa-collab">
      <ul>
        <li>I provide your CPA with clean, reconciled books organized by property and entity, so they can move quickly and accurately.</li>
        <li>I prepare supporting schedules including depreciation, loan amortization, and entity-level profit and loss statements.</li>
        <li>I communicate directly with your CPA during tax season to answer questions and provide any additional detail they need.</li>
        <li>I don't file your taxes. My job is to make sure your CPA has everything they need to do theirs, on time and without the back-and-forth.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- What I Don't Do -->
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">What I Don't Do</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); max-width: 42rem;">Knowing the boundaries upfront makes for a better working relationship. Here's what falls outside the scope of bookkeeping.</p>
    <div class="no-services">
      <div class="no-service-item">
        <h4>
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/>
            <line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/>
          </svg>
          No Tax Filing
        </h4>
        <p>I prepare your books for your CPA. I don't prepare or file tax returns. For tax filing, you need a licensed CPA or enrolled agent.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="no-service-item">
        <h4>
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/>
            <line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/>
          </svg>
          No Legal Advice
        </h4>
        <p>I can't advise on entity structure, contracts, or legal matters. For questions about LLCs, partnerships, or real estate law, consult a licensed attorney.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="no-service-item">
        <h4>
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/>
            <line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/>
          </svg>
          No Investment Advice
        </h4>
        <p>I track the numbers; I don't tell you what to buy, sell, or hold. For investment guidance on your real estate portfolio, consult a licensed financial advisor.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--space-xl);">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
